## Task Summary: per-worker CARGO_TARGET_DIR isolation

**Track:** per-worker-target-dir-2026-03-11
**Task:** Add WORKER_ID-based CARGO_TARGET_DIR separation for parallel Agent Teams builds
**Date:** 2026-03-12

### Changes

- compose.yml: CARGO_TARGET_DIR uses CARGO_TARGET_DIR_RELATIVE env var with "target" default
- compose.dev.yml: same CARGO_TARGET_DIR_RELATIVE change
- Makefile.toml: -exec tasks converted to script_runner with WORKER_ID-aware CARGO_TARGET_DIR override; prepare-local-cache-dirs creates worker-specific target dir
- .gitignore: added target-*/ pattern
- .claude/rules/07-dev-environment.md: added Parallel Worker Isolation (WORKER_ID) section
- scripts/test_verify_scripts.py: updated assertions for new compose env format and script-based test-one-exec

### Why

Parallel Agent Teams workers sharing a single tools-daemon container deadlock on target/ build locks. WORKER_ID env var enables per-worker CARGO_TARGET_DIR separation while keeping sccache shared for compilation cache efficiency. Default behavior (no WORKER_ID) remains unchanged.
